Taxi - Class in edu.trident.hilliard.finalassignment
Taxi models a taxi with a set rate and mileage rate, gas mileage, and gas capacity as well as currentGas, currentMileage, and totalFare to track information related to the specific taxi.

Variables:
RIDE_RATE - constant value for initial ride charge
RIDE_MILEAGE_RATE - constant value for per mile ride charge
GAS_MILEAGE - constant value for gas mileage of cab
GAS_CAPACITY - constant value for capacity of the cab's gas tank
currentGas - amount of gas in the cab
currentMileage - distance the cab has traveled
totalFare - accumulated total of fares
Taxi() - Constructor for class edu.trident.hilliard.finalassignment.Taxi
Constructor that creates a Taxi with base values of
RIDE_RATE = 2.0;
RIDE_MILEAGE_RATE = 0.585;
GAS_MILEAGE = 17.8;
currentGas = 22.9;
TaxiUI - Class in edu.trident.hilliard.finalassignment
TaxiUI creates and populates a JFrame with 3 JTextFields for GasInput, Input, and Output, a combo box and button to provide functionality of recording trips and adding gas, reporting gas, distance.

Variables:
currCab - RentedTaxi object that is currently selected in the UI
cabList - ArrayList of CabInfo records
cabs - ArrayList of RentedTaxi objects
cabDate - initialized as the last date of the cab
SERVICE_COST - constant value for the cost of servicing a cab
cabListPosition - tracks which cab is currently selected in the combo box
TaxiUI(ArrayList<RentedTaxi>, ArrayList<CabInfo>, String, String) - Constructor for class edu.trident.hilliard.finalassignment.TaxiUI
Constructor accepts a RentedTaxi object and an ArrayList of CabInfo records cabList is initialized for use by the UI and the last date of the first cab is requested through getLastDate as the cabDate
